                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>For the American Hebrew<lb/></p>
            <p>Messrs Editors<lb/></p>
            <p>Poverty is no shame.  My congregation has lost<lb/> much through adverse circumstances&#59; chiefly&#44; through<lb/> the death of very many old Israelites&#44; and the <del>growing</del> prevailing<lb/> indifference of the young.  But my congregation has<lb/> always <del>represented</del> held to one Idea&#44; and it will live&#44; or&#8212;if <del>so</del> otherwise decreed<lb/> above&#8212;die&#44; <del>while</del> still clinging to it.<lb/></p>
            <p>I <del>still</del> think <del>that</del> I may yet reckon <del>correct</del> on some who&#44; for the<lb/> sake of that Idea <del>alone</del>&#44; and not simply from personal<lb/> regard <del>respect</del> will impart fresh vigour to what has been al<lb/>lowed for a time to languish.  At all events&#44; it would be <del>too dear</del><lb/> <del>a sacrifice for the</del> a <sic>surrednery</sic> of principles in the KK &#34;Mickve Israel&#34; to purchase a longer<lb/> existence <del>by a surrendering of its leading principles</del> with the requested assistance of Hebrews avowedly opposed to its<lb/> <del>leading principles</del> conservative course.  The synagogue whose worship I<lb/> conduct shall not be thus supported with my expressed or tacit <del>approval</del> approval<lb/> <del>with</del> By the help of God and of men and women of our people&#44; who <del>trouble</del> deem<lb/> it right and beneficial to the Jewish cause to uphold <del>Jewish</del> &#34;conservatism&#44;&#34; it will overcome<lb/> present difficulties&#44; and <del>continue to</del> be as heretofore&#44; an instrument for good.<lb/>  And lest <del>my words</del> any should &#91;crossed&#45;out&#93; fancy that the Hazan and<lb/> his congregation <del>at</del> are at variance&#44; I declare that a<lb/> perfect accord of <del>religious</del> friendly sentiments exists&#44; and that I <del>per</del> cherish<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>a sense of high <del>regard</del> respect and appreciation for our active and <del>the endeavors of</del><lb/> <del>zeaus</del> zealous Parnass.<lb/></p>
            <p><del>Yours respectfully</del><lb/>
                S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia June 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1881.<lb/></p>
        </body>
